                    American Institute Of Electrical Engineers
                                 May 16th, 1888

The Chairman:—I have another    announcement to     make in
regard to Mr. Tesla's Motor. I    believe that    this motor—Mr.
Tesla can correct me if I am not    right—is   the first good alter-
nating current motor that has been    put    before the public any-
where—is that not so, Mr. Tesla?"  ''' — ''' "And he says that the system
can be seen in practical operation     at 89    Liberty street, second
floor, and he invites you all to    come and see    it." (Applause.)

