Dear Mr. Scherff,
————
by
Letter
June 28th, 1899


Under inclosure check for $300 to cover ongoing expenses. Will write more fully if I get any time to spare here at the research station although if Mister Astor inquires, please convey that while on the train coming here I enjoyed reading the copy he presented to me of his *JOURNEY IN OTHER WORLDS, with our views of possible interplantary civilizations aligning.
Otherwise please keep me posted the best you can on all.
Sincerely, N. Tesla


