      # Proof Offered of Existence
         Of Pure Magnetic Current #
                  —————
Discovery by Prof. Felix Ehrenhaft, if Con-
 firmed, Expected to Rank With Faraday
       Finding of Dynamo Principle
                  —————
MAGNETIC CURRENT DECLARED TO EXIST

“Prof. Felix Ehrenhaft, noted Vienna physicist, who fled after the Nazi occupation of Austria, presented yesterday before the American Physical Society, meeting at Columbia University, a set of his latest experiments, carried out in his laboratory in New York, which he said provided for the first time experimental proof of the existence of pure magnetic current.”…
______








New York Times, The   February 27th, 1944
     # Is There a Magnetic Current? #

"Last January Prof. Felix Ehrenhaft, an Austrian refugee who used to be director of the Physics Institute of the University of Vienna and who was highly regarded in pre-Hitler Europe, lectured before a local section of the American Physical Society and described some experiments which to him proved that magnetism flows in a current like electricity."…
______








New York Times, The   April 29th, 1944
           —————
   # OFFERS NEW TESTS
    ON MAGNETIC FLOW #
         —————
 Dr. Ehrenhaft Supports Idea
Such Currents Cover Universe,
     but He Is Challenged
         —————

“PITTSBURGH, April 28 -- Further experimental tests offered as evidence in support of his hypothesis that "not only electric currents but also magnetic currents flow through the universe" were described here today at the meeting of the American Physical Society, at the Mellon Institute, by Dr. Felix Ehrenhaft, Professor of Physics at the University of Vienna in the pre-Nazi era.”…
______








New York Times, The   June 25th, 1944
            —————
       # MAGNETIC MOTOR
         TAPS 'THIRD FORCE' #
            —————
 Prof. Ehrenhaft Demonstrates
    First Operation by Current
    From Permanent Magnet
            —————

“ROCHESTER, June 24 -- What was said to be the first magnetic motor, operating purely on magnetic current supplied by a permanent magnet, was demonstrated here today before the meeting of the American Physical Society at the University of Rochester by Prof. Felix Ehrenhaft, who recently startled the scientific world with experiments which, he maintains, provide proof for the existence of pure magnetic current.”…
